    <note>Lu(2) Youkai [15014] Zheng Xie, WJ, 22.4a-7b has inscription for wife, born Li, who married him at age of 16 and died in 1061 at age 42. According to Zheng(1) Xie [13378], her ancestry--father, Zhouxun [20034], grandfather, Ding(5) [20033], and great grandfather, Jing(5) [20032] (all had civil offices)--was very distinguished and usually intermarried with elite families (gui) and while the Lu(2) had past distinction of multigenerational high office-holding, the background of Youkai was was ru (classicist). I cannot identify her family. The ancestry of Zhao(1) Kejie's [20035] wife was exactly the same except that the generation for Jing(5) and Ding(5) are reversed. They are identified as Wen people, but Wen is not an administrative unit, but does probably refer to the area around a river in central Shandong. CBD, 5, 3822.</note>
